<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Gorge2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Gorge,</orth> vb. to glut, to fill: <cit><quote>the --d hawk,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 694" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 694</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with his presence glutted, --d and full,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.2.84" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 2, 84</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.120" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 120</bibl>. Absol.: <cit><quote>--ing and feeding from our soldiers' hands,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 5.1.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. V, 1, 82</bibl></cit>. cf. <emph>Full-gorged.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>